        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 5:13PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 513 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Matoaca, or near Virginia State University, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Petersburg, Colonial Heights, Chester, Fort Gregg-Adams, Virginia
State University, Ettrick, and Matoaca around 520 PM EDT.
Hopewell around 525 PM EDT.
Jordans Point around 540 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Burgess, Wayside,
Birchett Estate, Addison, Jordan Point Country Club, Petersburg
National Battlefield, Glendale, New Bohemia, Richmond International,
and Petersburg Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
